<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently, PartialLoop checks to see if $model implements toArray(), and, if so, uses that method to cast to an array. However, this is not always the desired behavior -- in the case of a Zend_Db_Table_Rowset, the developer may want to pass the individual rows as objects to the partial, allowing the ability to call methods on it.</p>

<p>The behavior should be changed; if the object implements Traversable, PartialLoop should simply iterate over it.</p>

